The steps to Connecting to a DB with JDBC:
  1. Create a Db/Schema to connect to
  2. Ensure the appropriate Driver is added tot he project build path
  3. Open a connection to the MySQL Server
  4. Create a Statement Object
  5. Execute Statement object query
  6. Process the ResultSet from the query execution
  7. Close your objects and the connection

executeQuery() will return a ResultSet and is generally used for select queries ona  DB sinc ethey return results
updateQuery() will return an int detailing how many rows were affecte by the query
next() Moves the cursor to the next row in the ResultSet

All 3 can be seen being utilized in the DBUtilities Class included in the Repo.
